<title>USA: Citizens names Mark Oliver president.</title>
<headline>Citizens names Mark Oliver president.</headline>
<dateline>AUSTIN, Texas 1997-03-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Citizens Inc on Tuesday said Mark Oliver was named president and chief administrative officer of Citizens and its subsidiary companies.</p>
<p>Oliver replaces James Dunham, who resigned in December 1996 to pursue personal interests.</p>
<p>Oliver has served in several positions in the company since 1984, including vice president/controller, and chief financial officer, the company said.</p>
